submission to the Department of Immigration and Citizenship, Australia&rsquo;s
Humanitarian Program 2013&ndash;14 and beyond</em></a>, January 2013.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref131" name="_ftn131" title="">[131]</a>.             Liberal
Party of Australia and the Nationals, <a
href="http://parlinfo.aph.gov.au/parlInfo/search/display/display.w3p;query=Id%3A%22library%2Fpartypol%2F2666247%22"><em>The
Coalition policy to clear Labor&rsquo;s 30,000 border failure backlog</em></a>, op.
cit.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref132" name="_ftn132" title="">[132]</a>.             DIBP,
<a
href="https://www.border.gov.au/Lega/Lega/Form/Immi-FAQs/what-changes-have-been-made-to-priority-processing-for-family-stream-visa"><em>What
changes have been made to priority processing for family stream visa
applications sponsored by illegal maritime arrivals (IMAs)?</em></a>, DIBP
website; and Liberal Party of Australia and the Nationals, <a
href="http://parlinfo.aph.gov.au/parlInfo/search/display/display.w3p;query=Id%3A%22library%2Fpartypol%2F2480348%22"><em>Our
plan: real solutions for all Australians &ndash; the direction, values and policy
priorities of the next Coalition Government</em></a>, op. cit.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref133" name="_ftn133" title="">[133]</a>.             UNHCR,
<a href="http://www.unhcr.org/global-trends-2015.html"><em>Global trends 2015</em></a>,
UNHCR website, 2016.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref134" name="_ftn134" title="">[134]</a>.             A
Keski-Nummi, &lsquo;A place of refuge: responses to international population
movements&rsquo;, in B Douglas and J Wodak (eds), <a
href="http://www.australia21.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/AWRefugee-and-asylum-seeker-policy-Finding-a-better-way.Essays1.pdf"><em>Refugees
and asylum seekers: finding a better way</em></a>, op. cit.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref135" name="_ftn135" title="">[135]</a>.             Expert
Panel on Asylum Seekers, <a
href="http://dpl/Books/2012/ExpertPanelOnAsylumSeekers.pdf"><em>Report of the
Expert Panel on Asylum Seekers</em></a>, op. cit.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref136" name="_ftn136" title="">[136]</a>. D Corlett, op.
cit.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref137" name="_ftn137" title="">[137]</a>.             For
an example of these perceptions see A K Hekmat, &lsquo;<a
href="http://parlinfo.aph.gov.au/parlInfo/search/display/display.w3p;query=Id%3A%22media%2Fpressclp%2F452799%22">We
asylum seekers risk boats because it is our only option</a>&rsquo;, <em>Sydney Morning
Herald</em>, 27&nbsp;December 2010, p. 11.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref138" name="_ftn138" title="">[138]</a>.             E
Feller, &lsquo;Boats: what to do? A practitioners viewpoint&rsquo;, op. cit. See also
Professor J McAdam, &lsquo;Leading on protection&rsquo;, in B Douglas and J Wodak (eds), <a
href="http://www.australia21.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/AWRefugee-and-asylum-seeker-policy-Finding-a-better-way.Essays1.pdf"><em>Refugees
and asylum seekers: finding a better way</em></a>, op. cit.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref139" name="_ftn139" title="">[139]</a>.             UNHCR,
<a href="http://www.refworld.org/docid/4e92d7c32.html"><em>Regional cooperative
approach to address refugees, asylum seekers and irregular movement</em></a>,
UNHCR Discussion paper, November 2011, UNHCR website; and A Guterres (United
Nations High Commissioner for Refugees), <a
href="http://parlinfo.aph.gov.au/parlInfo/search/display/display.w3p;query=Id%3A%22library%2Fjrnart%2F1423077%22"><em>The
changing face of global displacement: responses and responsibilities</em>,</a>
address to the Lowy Institute for International Policy, Sydney, 14 February
2012.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref140" name="_ftn140" title="">[140]</a>.             <strong>J Menadue, </strong>A Keski-Nummi and K Gauthier<a
href="http://cpd.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/CPD-Refugee_Report_Web.pdf">, <em>A new approach:
breaking the stalemate on refugees and asylum seekers</em></a><strong>, Centre for Policy Development, Sydney, August 2011, </strong>p.
313.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref141" name="_ftn141" title="">[141]</a>.             A
Keski-Nummi, op. cit.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref142" name="_ftn142" title="">[142]</a>.             UNHCR,
<a
href="http://web.archive.org/web/20140212161745/http:/unhcr.org.au/unhcr/images/e-Newsletter%20December%202013.pdf"><em>Refugee
newsletter</em></a>, op. cit.</p>





<p><a href="#_ftnref143" name="_ftn143" title="">[143]</a>.             See
P Power, &lsquo;Ten incremental steps to transform refugee protection in the Asia
Pacific region&rsquo;, in B Douglas and J Wodak (eds), <a
href="http://www.australia21.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/AWRefugee-and-asylum-seeker-policy-Finding-a-better-way.Essays1.pdf"><em>Refugees
and asylum seekers: finding a better way</em></a>, op. cit.; D Corlett, op.
cit.; and A Keski-Nummi, op. cit.</p>


